Harry Keenan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_Keenan 0 Harry George Keenan (June 15, 1867, Richmond, Indiana – April 18, 1944, Santa Ana, California) was an early American silent film actor. He starred in about 45 silent films mostly shot between 1912 and 1916, including The Highest Bid, with actresses such as Charlotte Burton.
